Program: Discovery
Title: Life story - the Cambrian period
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxqh
Last Broadcast Date: 07 December 2000
Life in the Cambrian period, 500 million years ago. A time when early multi-cellular forms of life lived on the sea floor and some had even made it to live on the land. Fossils help us to explain exactly how these creatures lived.